An IP Address is adminsitered for each computer, like an ID number. The Domain Name Service, or DNS, translates and converts the IP address so that it is recognized and can make entry.

Cookies are the user's information when visiting a website. Because of cookies, Facebook is able to recognize who wishes to login to its site.

The three basic parts that make up a Uniform Resource Locator, or URL, are the protocol, the domain name, and the path.
